title.narrative: SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: The equity, child focus and adaptive capacity of Government national social protection programmes are strengthened., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Cross Sectoral - Children With Disabilities, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid), Evaluation, Reducing Child Poverty, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, the most disadvantaged children, families and communities in remote rural areas and impoverished urban pockets have access to inclusive systems that protect them from poverty and enhance their ability to appropriately respond to emergencies and climate change risks.

description.narrative: Social protection remained an important intervention in the government&39;s response to the;COVID19 pandemic. UNICEF&39;s sustained;engagement with government and partners has made visible the child poverty effects of the pandemic and limitations of the government&39;s social protection response in addressing poverty.;In BARMM, UNICEF&39;s strategic focus on systems strengthening contributed to laying the building blocks of a risk informed and shock responsive social protection system beginning with an inclusive poverty registry design which;is expected to reduce exclusion in the delivery of social assistance and improve the life chances of Bangsamoro children and their families.;;;; ; ; ;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/12/2021
